3.2 How to Automatically Turn On Highlights after Re-starting Emacs
===================================================================

It is recommended that ‘org-remark-global-tracking-mode’ be turned on as
part of your Emacs initialization.  This should be done before you start
adding highlights in any file.

Once you have added highlights to some files, quit Emacs, and re-start
it, active ‘org-remark-global-tracking-mode’ will automatically turn on
‘org-remark-mode’ and load the highlights from your previous sessions
for the files being globally tracked.

Without this global minor mode, you would need to remember to activate
‘org-remark-mode’ for each file where you add highlights and annotation.
This is often unpractical.


